kind of bringing to this discussion.

00:01:19.640 --> 00:01:21.380
We're not simply thinking about it,

00:01:21.410 --> 00:01:24.060
philosophising about it
and speculating about it.

00:01:24.090 --> 00:01:29.930
We have deep convictions born
out of unusual experiences.

00:01:29.960 --> 00:01:31.930
Why don't you speak first?

00:01:31.960 --> 00:01:33.020
It's true.

00:01:33.040 --> 00:01:34.380
It's why-- it's in a way that's brought us

00:01:34.410 --> 00:01:38.160
together around these-- to
do these dialogues, I think.

00:01:38.360 --> 00:01:40.210
And I was just explaining to-- you

00:01:40.240 --> 00:01:45.800
know, that to discriminate the difference
between knowledge and wisdom.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:46.980
You know, so, although

00:01:47.010 --> 00:01:53.120
we've explored strains of knowledge in
this, wisdom is different from knowledge.

00:01:53.360 --> 00:01:55.260
It's the opposite in a way, because,

00:01:55.290 --> 00:01:59.420
for me, the way I understand wisdom is
that wisdom comes through revelation.

00:01:59.450 --> 00:02:01.400
It comes through listening.

00:02:01.640 --> 00:02:04.700
It comes through being
passive and then receiving.

00:02:04.720 --> 00:02:06.900
Whereas knowledge is something
that you do opposite.

00:02:06.930 --> 00:02:10.610
You go after it,
you chase it, you hunt it,

00:02:10.640 --> 00:02:15.300
you know. You're going towards it, instead
of allowing it to come towards you.

00:02:15.320 --> 00:02:16.640
And so

00:02:17.680 --> 00:02:19.200
you get different

00:02:19.640 --> 00:02:20.680
information

00:02:20.800 --> 00:02:22.400
through revelation.

00:02:23.120 --> 00:02:26.100
And it's not information in the same way.

00:02:26.120 --> 00:02:27.560
It's cellular.

00:02:29.200 --> 00:02:30.480
You know, so my experience

00:02:31.280 --> 00:02:39.920
that's led to me being me, and doing what
I do, is because I have always had this,

00:02:41.080 --> 00:02:46.880
